POST /api/live.  (application/json)
POST
/api/live
API endpoint to push the battery status to Onbalansmarkt.com.


LiveDataPushRequestCollapse allobject
Push live data to the Onbalansmarkt platform

timestampCollapse allstring
Timestamp of measurement in ISO8601 format, i.e. 2021-01-01T12:00:00Z

Examples
#0"2025-01-20T16:00:00Z"
batteryResult
Net daily result achieved by the battery in euros.

Examples
#0"8.80"
batteryResultTotal
Net all time result achieved by the battery in euros.

Examples
#0"1004.75"
batteryResultEpex
Optional gross battery result on the EPEX market, typically the charging costs.

Examples
#0"-1.40"
batteryResultImbalance
Optional gross battery result on the imbalance market, without taking losses and costs into account.

Examples
#0"9.60"
batteryResultCustom
Optional provider-specific battery trading result, such as a loyalty or trade provider specific incentive.

Examples
#0"0.60"
batteryResultAccounting
Optional accounting transaction ('totaal te verrekenen'), indicating the net transaction the provider will make at the end of the month.

Examples
#0"0.60"
batteryCharge
Current charge of the battery in %, 0-100, optional but recommended.

Examples
#0"76"
batteryPower
Current power of the battery in Watt, optional.

Examples
#0"-9000"

chargedToday
kWh charged ('consumed') by the battery as a positive number, optional but recommended.
Examples

dischargedToday
kWh discharged ('produced') by the battery as a positive number, optional but recommended.

Examples
#0"8"


loadBalancingActive
Indicates whether load balancing is active, limiting the current battery output, set to 'on' or 'off', optional.
Enum
#0"on"
#1"off"

solarResult
Daily result achieved by the solar panels in euros, optional.

chargerResult
Daily result achieved by the charger in euros, optional.


totalBatteryCycles
Total number of battery cycles that the battery has gone through in its lifetime, optional.
Examples
#0"143"


mode
Optional battery operating mode, can be provided to override the mode configured on the profile page. The available options vary by provider but include: imbalance, manual, day_ahead (, self_consumption, self_consumption_plus, imbalance_aggressive
Enum
#0"imbalance"
#1"imbalance_aggressive"
#2"manual"
#3"day_ahead"
#4"self_consumption"
#5"self_consumption_plus"


